The saga continues as award-winning filmmaker Denis Villeneuve embarks on â€œDune: Part Two,â€ the next chapter of Frank Herbertâ€™s celebrated novel Dune, with an expanded all-star international ensemble cast.  The film, from Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures, is the highly anticipated follow-up to 2021â€™s six-time Academy Award-winning â€œDune.â€
The big-screen epic continues the adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s acclaimed bestseller Dune with returning and new stars, including Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œWonka,â€ â€œCall Me by Your Nameâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: No Way Home,â€ â€œMalcolm & Marie,â€ â€œEuphoriaâ€), Rebecca Ferguson (â€œMission: Impossible â€“ Dead Reckoningâ€), Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œAvengers: End Game,â€ â€œMilkâ€), Oscar nominee Austin Butler (â€œElvis,â€ â€œOnce Upon A Timeâ€¦In Hollywoodâ€), Oscar nominee Florence Pugh (â€œBlack Widow,â€ â€œLittle Womenâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œThor: Love and Thunderâ€), Oscar winner Christopher Walken (â€œThe Deer Hunter,â€ â€œHairsprayâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), LÃ©a Seydoux (the â€œJames Bondâ€ franchise and â€œCrimes of the Futureâ€), with Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (the â€œMamma Mia!â€ films, â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œBeing the Ricardosâ€).
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee. 
Villeneuve directed from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts based on Herbertâ€™s novel.  The film is produced by Mary Parent, Cale Boyter, Villeneuve, Tanya Lapointe and Patrick McCormick.  The executive producers are Josh Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt, Kim Herbert, with Kevin J. Anderson serving as creative consultant.
Villeneuve is again collaborating with his â€œDuneâ€ creatives: Oscar-winning director of photography Greig Fraser; Oscar-winning production designer Patrice Vermette; Oscar-winning editor Joe Walker; Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert; Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West.  Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer is again on hand to create the score.
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ was filmed on location in Budapest, Abu Dhabi, Jordan and Italy.  The film is slated for a November 3, 2023 worldwide release from Warner Bros. Pictures.

title: Prime Minister's Questions (PMQs) - 3 May 2023
description:
The British Sign Language (BSL) version on Parliament Live TV is available here: https://parliamentlive.tv/event/index/05376c02-07ff-4d4d-a898-2fe0d0b1db72?in=12:01:27
Or watch on YouTube:  https://youtu.be/-8jEZpfPjws

Prime Minister's Question Time, also referred to as PMQs, takes place every Wednesday the House of Commons sits. It gives MPs the chance to put questions to the Prime Minister, Rishi Sunak MP.

In most cases, the session starts with a routine 'open question' from an MP about the Prime Minister's engagements. MPs can then ask supplementary questions on any subject, often one of current political significance.

The Leader of the Opposition, Sir Keir Starmer MP, asks six questions and the leader of the second largest opposition party asks two. If another minister takes the place of the Prime Minister, opposition parties will usually nominate a shadow minister to ask the questions.

Want to find out more about what's happening in the House of Commons this week? Follow the House of Commons on:

title: Ik Sloot 20 YouTubers Op In Een Villa!
description:
Een hele goede nacht! Maar in jullie geval middag! Want ik zit in New York! Hier is het 6 uur eerder! Waarom zet ik achter elke zin een uitroepteken? In ieder geval, hallo! Doe ik het toch weer. Deze keer hebben we echt een pareltje van een video gemaakt, of kan ik beter zeggen, documentaire? Want poepoe, wat een video. De lengte, de kwaliteit, de humor, de spanning, het heeft alle recepten dat een video goed maakt. Kijk ook is naar die titel en thumbnail... daar klik je toch meteen op? Jij als het goed is sowieso, anders lees je dit niet.  Misschien dacht je zelfs dat het clickbait was want: "20 youtubers op 1 plek? dat kan toch helemaal niet?". Daar heb je helemaal gelijk in, maar eigenlijk ook weer niet, want het is toch gelukt. Maarja daarom duurde het toch weer bijna 2 weken tot deze video online is gekomen, want potjandorie, wat haat ik YouTubers toch. Behalve Hein, maar die is eigenlijk ook geen YouTuber. De rest haat ik wel. Nee grapje, ik hou stuk voor stuk allemaal inmens van ze. Behalve Hein. Die vind ik gewoon aardig, maar die is eigenlijk ook geen YouTuber. Maar dat had ik al gezegd... The big-screen epic continues the adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s acclaimed bestseller Dune with returning and new stars, including Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œWonka,â€ â€œCall Me by Your Nameâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: No Way Home,â€ â€œMalcolm & Marie,â€ â€œEuphoriaâ€), Rebecca Ferguson (â€œMission: Impossible â€“ Dead Reckoningâ€), Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œAvengers: End Game,â€ â€œMilkâ€), Oscar nominee Austin Butler (â€œElvis,â€ â€œOnce Upon A Timeâ€¦In Hollywoodâ€), Oscar nominee Florence Pugh (â€œBlack Widow,â€ â€œLittle Womenâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œThor: Love and Thunderâ€), Oscar winner Christopher Walken (â€œThe Deer Hunter,â€ â€œHairsprayâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), LÃ©a Seydoux (the â€œJames Bondâ€ franchise and â€œCrimes of the Futureâ€), with Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (the â€œMamma Mia!â€ films, â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œBeing the Ricardosâ€).

The executive producers are Josh Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt, Kim Herbert, with Kevin J. Anderson serving as creative consultant.
Villeneuve is again collaborating with his â€œDuneâ€ creatives: Oscar-winning director of photography Greig Fraser; Oscar-winning production designer Patrice Vermette; Oscar-winning editor Joe Walker; Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert; Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West.  Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer is again on hand to create the score.

The saga continues as award-winning filmmaker Denis Villeneuve embarks on â€œDune: Part Two,â€ the next chapter of Frank Herbertâ€™s celebrated novel Dune, with an expanded all-star international ensemble cast.  The film, from Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures, is the highly anticipated follow-up to 2021â€™s six-time Academy Award-winning â€œDune.â€
The big-screen epic continues the adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s acclaimed bestseller Dune with returning and new stars, including Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œWonka,â€ â€œCall Me by Your Nameâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: No Way Home,â€ â€œMalcolm & Marie,â€ â€œEuphoriaâ€), Rebecca Ferguson (â€œMission: Impossible â€“ Dead Reckoningâ€), Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œAvengers: End Game,â€ â€œMilkâ€), Oscar nominee Austin Butler (â€œElvis,â€ â€œOnce Upon A Timeâ€¦In Hollywoodâ€), Oscar nominee Florence Pugh (â€œBlack Widow,â€ â€œLittle Womenâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œThor: Love and Thunderâ€), Oscar winner Christopher Walken (â€œThe Deer Hunter,â€ â€œHairsprayâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), LÃ©a Seydoux (the â€œJames Bondâ€ franchise and â€œCrimes of the Futureâ€), with Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (the â€œMamma Mia!â€ films, â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œBeing the Ricardosâ€).
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee. 
Villeneuve directed from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts based on Herbertâ€™s novel.  The film is produced by Mary Parent, Cale Boyter, Villeneuve, Tanya Lapointe and Patrick McCormick.  The executive producers are Josh Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt, Kim Herbert, with Kevin J. Anderson serving as creative consultant.
Villeneuve is again collaborating with his â€œDuneâ€ creatives: Oscar-winning director of photography Greig Fraser; Oscar-winning production designer Patrice Vermette; Oscar-winning editor Joe Walker; Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert; Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West.  Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer is again on hand to create the score.
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ was filmed on location in Budapest, Abu Dhabi, Jordan and Italy.  The film is slated for a November 3, 2023 worldwide release from Warner Bros. Pictures.

The saga continues as award-winning filmmaker Denis Villeneuve embarks on â€œDune: Part Two,â€ the next chapter of Frank Herbertâ€™s celebrated novel Dune, with an expanded all-star international ensemble cast.  The film, from Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures, is the highly anticipated follow-up to 2021â€™s six-time Academy Award-winning â€œDune.â€
The big-screen epic continues the adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s acclaimed bestseller Dune with returning and new stars, including Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œWonka,â€ â€œCall Me by Your Nameâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: No Way Home,â€ â€œMalcolm & Marie,â€ â€œEuphoriaâ€), Rebecca Ferguson (â€œMission: Impossible â€“ Dead Reckoningâ€), Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œAvengers: End Game,â€ â€œMilkâ€), Oscar nominee Austin Butler (â€œElvis,â€ â€œOnce Upon A Timeâ€¦In Hollywoodâ€), Oscar nominee Florence Pugh (â€œBlack Widow,â€ â€œLittle Womenâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œThor: Love and Thunderâ€), Oscar winner Christopher Walken (â€œThe Deer Hunter,â€ â€œHairsprayâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), LÃ©a Seydoux (the â€œJames Bondâ€ franchise and â€œCrimes of the Futureâ€), with Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (the â€œMamma Mia!â€ films, â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œBeing the Ricardosâ€).
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee. 
Villeneuve directed from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts based on Herbertâ€™s novel.  The film is produced by Mary Parent, Cale Boyter, Villeneuve, Tanya Lapointe and Patrick McCormick.  The executive producers are Josh Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt, Kim Herbert, with Kevin J. Anderson serving as creative consultant.
Villeneuve is again collaborating with his â€œDuneâ€ creatives: Oscar-winning director of photography Greig Fraser; Oscar-winning production designer Patrice Vermette; Oscar-winning editor Joe Walker; Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert; Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West.  Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer is again on hand to create the score.
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ was filmed on location in Budapest, Abu Dhabi, Jordan and Italy.  The film is slated for a November 3, 2023 worldwide release from Warner Bros. Pictures.

title: Starship Flight Test
description:
Starship gave us quite a show during todayâ€™s first flight test of a fully integrated Starship and Super Heavy rocket from Starbase in Texas. 
 
At 8:33 a.m. CT, Starship successfully lifted off from the orbital launch pad for the first time. The vehicle cleared the pad and beach as Starship climbed to an apogee of ~39 km over the Gulf of Mexico â€“ the highest of any Starship to-date. The vehicle experienced multiple engines out during the flight test, lost altitude, and began to tumble. The flight termination system was commanded on both the booster and ship. As is standard procedure, the pad and surrounding area was cleared well in advance of the test, and we expect the road and beach near the pad to remain closed until tomorrow.

With a test like this, success comes from what we learn, and we learned a tremendous amount about the vehicle and ground systems today that will help us improve on future flights of Starship.
 
Thank you to our customers, Cameron County, and the wider community for the continued support and encouragement. And congratulations to the entire SpaceX team on an exciting first flight test of Starship!

The saga continues as award-winning filmmaker Denis Villeneuve embarks on â€œDune: Part Two,â€ the next chapter of Frank Herbertâ€™s celebrated novel Dune, with an expanded all-star international ensemble cast.  The film, from Warner Bros. Pictures and Legendary Pictures, is the highly anticipated follow-up to 2021â€™s six-time Academy Award-winning â€œDune.â€
The big-screen epic continues the adaptation of Frank Herbertâ€™s acclaimed bestseller Dune with returning and new stars, including Oscar nominee TimothÃ©e Chalamet (â€œWonka,â€ â€œCall Me by Your Nameâ€), Zendaya (â€œSpider-Man: No Way Home,â€ â€œMalcolm & Marie,â€ â€œEuphoriaâ€), Rebecca Ferguson (â€œMission: Impossible â€“ Dead Reckoningâ€), Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (â€œAvengers: End Game,â€ â€œMilkâ€), Oscar nominee Austin Butler (â€œElvis,â€ â€œOnce Upon A Timeâ€¦In Hollywoodâ€), Oscar nominee Florence Pugh (â€œBlack Widow,â€ â€œLittle Womenâ€), Dave Bautista (the â€œGuardians of the Galaxyâ€ films, â€œThor: Love and Thunderâ€), Oscar winner Christopher Walken (â€œThe Deer Hunter,â€ â€œHairsprayâ€), Stephen McKinley Henderson (â€œFences,â€ â€œLady Birdâ€), LÃ©a Seydoux (the â€œJames Bondâ€ franchise and â€œCrimes of the Futureâ€), with Stellan SkarsgÃ¥rd (the â€œMamma Mia!â€ films, â€œAvengers: Age of Ultronâ€), with Oscar nominee Charlotte Rampling (â€œ45 Years,â€ â€œAssassinâ€™s Creedâ€), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (â€œNo Country for Old Men,â€ â€œBeing the Ricardosâ€).
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ will explore the mythic journey of Paul Atreides as he unites with Chani and the Fremen while on a warpath of revenge against the conspirators who destroyed his family. Facing a choice between the love of his life and the fate of the known universe, he endeavors to prevent a terrible future only he can foresee. 
Villeneuve directed from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts based on Herbertâ€™s novel.  The film is produced by Mary Parent, Cale Boyter, Villeneuve, Tanya Lapointe and Patrick McCormick.  The executive producers are Josh Grode, Herbert W. Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt, Kim Herbert, with Kevin J. Anderson serving as creative consultant.
Villeneuve is again collaborating with his â€œDuneâ€ creatives: Oscar-winning director of photography Greig Fraser; Oscar-winning production designer Patrice Vermette; Oscar-winning editor Joe Walker; Oscar-winning visual effects supervisor Paul Lambert; Oscar-nominated costume designer Jacqueline West.  Oscar-winning composer Hans Zimmer is again on hand to create the score.
â€œDune: Part Twoâ€ was filmed on location in Budapest, Abu Dhabi, Jordan and Italy.  The film is slated for a November 3, 2023 worldwide release from Warner Bros. Pictures.
